  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 7db8e45de40bae34aa413d41ea107b72, type: 3}
  m_Name: Topic_WhyBuiltIt
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::TombOfServilii.TopicData
  topicTitle: Why was it built?
  contentText: Like many Roman tombs along major consular roads, it was built outside
    the city walls (due to Roman law) to preserve the memory of the deceased, showcase
    the family's patrician status, wealth, and civic contributions to travelers entering
    Rome.
  narrationClip: {fileID: 0}
  subtitleText: It was built outside the city walls to preserve memory and showcase
    the family's patrician status.
